Mr. Williams often butted heads with Gordy, and he said he was fired and rehired at least five times in four years.
“You had to maintain the Motown image 24 hours a day or you’d lose your job,” Mr. Williams recalled in 1996.
Returning to Chicago, Mr. Williams became an independent producer.
ADIn later years, Mr. Williams struggled with drug and alcohol addiction.
By his own account, Mr. Williams was a miscreant while in high school.